# Phase 3, Step 6: Visualization — Seeing the Swarm

Add a live dashboard, standalone task board, dry-run mode, and summary event system.

## Goal

Make the swarm's state visible. Add an Ink-based CLI dashboard for swarm mode, a standalone `npm run viz` task board, a dry-run mode that tests the full flow without API calls, and a summary event system that announces project completion.

## Requirements

- `src/summary.ts` — summary event system
  - `Summary` interface: project name, subtask results, final text
  - `onSummary(callback)` to subscribe, `emitSummary(summary)` to publish
- `src/viz.ts` — standalone task board
  - Reads `tasks.db` directly, renders ANSI-colored tree
  - Refreshes every 500ms, uses alternate screen buffer
  - Run via `npm run viz`
- `src/dashboard.tsx` — integrated Ink dashboard
  - Three zones: scrolling logs (Static), live task board, input line
  - `console.log` redirected into log buffer
  - SummaryBox appears on project completion
  - `startDashboard(onInput)` public API
  - `pushSummary(summary)` pushes to dashboard panel
- `src/llm.ts` — dry-run mode
  - `DRY_RUN=1` env var replaces LLM with mock
  - Orchestrator gets canned `create_project` call
  - Other agents get text completions
- `src/index.ts` — integration
  - Swarm mode: start dashboard before spawning agents, subscribe to summaries
  - Solo mode: print summaries to console
- `src/task-queue.ts` — summary emission
  - `complete()` checks `reply_to === "user"` and calls `emitSummary()`
- `package.json` — new deps: `ink`, `react`, `@types/react`; new script: `viz`
- `tsconfig.json` — add `"jsx": "react-jsx"`
- `.gitignore` — add `temp_*`

## What changes from Phase 3 Step 5

- Added: `src/summary.ts`, `src/viz.ts`, `src/dashboard.tsx`
- Modified: `src/llm.ts` — dry-run mode
- Modified: `src/index.ts` — dashboard + summary integration
- Modified: `src/task-queue.ts` — emitSummary on reply_to
- Modified: `package.json` — deps + viz script
- Modified: `tsconfig.json` — jsx support
- Modified: `.gitignore` — temp files
